PROJECT-1
                                         REPORT ANALYSIS
1.VPC Creation:
 1.1 Open the AWS management console and navigate to vpc
 1.2 Select create vpc and choose vpc and more
 1.3 Configure the ipv4 CIDR block,availability zones,and public/private
subnets
 1.4 Create the vpc and verify the resource map

2.EC2 Creation:
 2.1 Navigate to the EC2 dashboard
 2.2 Launch an ubuntu instance
 2.3 Create or select an existing key pair
 2.4 Configure network settings using the custom vpc

3.Connecting to EC2 using MobaXterm:
 3.1 Open MobaXterm
 3.2 Create an SSH session using the EC2 public IP address
 3.3 Set the username as ubuntu
 3.4 Import the .pem key file and connect

4.Installing Python:
 -> sudo apt update
 -> sudo apt install python3 -y
 -> sudo apt install python3-pip -y
 -> python3 -m http.sever 8000

 OUTPUT-http://<EC2_PUBLIC_IP>:8000

5.Configure Security:
 5.1 Add an inbound security group rule to allow TCP traffic on port 8000
 5.2 Configure NACL rules to test traffic blocking and filtering

SUMMARY:
      This project demonstrates deploying a python web server on AWS
infrastructure.A custom VPC was created eith specific CIDR
blocks,availability zones,and public/private subnets,followed by launching
an ubuntu EC2 instance connected to the VPC.Remote access to the EC2
instance was established using MobaXterm via an SSH session with a .pem key
file.Python3 and pip were installed on the instance,and a simple HTTP
server was hosted on port 8000,accessible via the EC2's public
IP.Finally,security was configured by adding inbound security group rules
and NACL rules to control and test TCP traffic on port 8000.

